Junction	#43.	 tie, pinion, string, strap, sew, lace, tat, stitch, tack, knit, button, buckle, hitch, lash, truss, bandage, braid, splice, swathe, gird, tether, moor, picket, harness, chain
Crossing	#219.	 anastomose [Med.], inosculate, dovetail, splice, link
Interposition	#228.	 let in, dovetail, splice, mortise
Restoration	#660.	 stop a gap, stanch, staunch, caulk, calk, careen, splice, bind up wounds. Adj. restored &c. v.
Drunkenness	#959.	 have one's swill [Slang], drain the cup, splice the main brace, take a hair of the dog that bit you. liquor, liquor up
